-- Octopus Holdings Appoints John Strickland as Chairman as Leong Retires
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-19T21:34:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/octopus-holdings-appoints-john-strickland-as-chairman-as-leong-retires.html
Octopus Holdings Ltd. has apppointed
 John Strickland  as non-executive chairman effective Jan. 1,
replacing the retiring  Lincoln Leong , the company said in a
press release on its website yesterday.  U.K.-born Strickland, 70, is a former chairman of HSBC
Plc’s Asian unit Hongkong & Shanghai Banking Corp. and is the
current chairman of the Hong Kong Internet Registration Corp.
and the Hong Kong Domain Name Registration Co. He’s also a non-
executive director on the boards of Hong Kong Exchanges &
Clearing Ltd, IDS Group Ltd, and Esquel Holdings Inc.  Leong has been Octopus chairman for more than nine years,
according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  